        <Notes>k__BackingField:
        - <Pos>k__BackingField: {x: 5840, y: 11360}
          <RawContent>k__BackingField: "<p>To begin, press the <strong>Play (\u25B6\uFE0F)</strong>
            button in the top menu to enter <a target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer
            nofollow\" href=\"https://docs.arcweave.com/project-tools/play-mode/overview\"><strong>Play
            Mode</strong></a>.</p><p>If you\u2019ve played other Arcweave projects
            before, you\u2019ll already be familiar with Play Mode.</p><p>This project,
            however, makes use of the <a target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer
            nofollow\" href=\"https://docs.arcweave.com/project-tools/play-mode/style-editor\"><strong>Style
            Editor</strong></a> to create the classic visual novel look, instead
            of relying on Arcweave\u2019s default CSS.</p>"
          <ColorTheme>k__BackingField: lightBlue
        - <Pos>k__BackingField: {x: 6280, y: 11800}
          <RawContent>k__BackingField: '<p>Add audio to your elements so it plays
            during Play Mode.</p><p>To do this, drag an <a target="_blank" rel="noopener
            noreferrer nofollow" href="https://docs.arcweave.com/project-items/assets/audio"><strong>audio
            asset</strong></a> from the <a target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer
            nofollow" href="https://docs.arcweave.com/project-items/assets/overview"><strong>Assets</strong></a>
            section in the left sidebar and drop it into the element.</p><p>Click
            on the attached audio asset to set its behavior: play once, loop, or
            stop.</p>'
          <ColorTheme>k__BackingField: lightBlue
        - <Pos>k__BackingField: {x: 5840, y: 11160}
          <RawContent>k__BackingField: <p>Welcome! This tutorial will guide you through
            creating a <a target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer nofollow" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Visual_novel"><strong>visual
            novel</strong></a> in Arcweave.</p><p>For broader Arcweave fundamentals,
            check out the <strong>Interactive Fiction</strong> example in the <a
            target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer nofollow" href="https://docs.arcweave.com/workspaces/projects#project-templates">project
            templates</a>.</p>
          <ColorTheme>k__BackingField: pink
        - <Pos>k__BackingField: {x: 7200, y: 11720}
          <RawContent>k__BackingField: <p>The wide image (your scene's background)
            is an <a target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer nofollow" href="https://docs.arcweave.com/project-items/elements#setting-a-cover"><strong>element
            cover</strong></a>. To add one, drag an <a target="_blank" rel="noopener
            noreferrer nofollow" href="https://docs.arcweave.com/project-items/assets/images"><strong>image
            asset</strong></a> from the <strong>Assets</strong> section (left sidebar)
            and drop it into the element.</p>
          <ColorTheme>k__BackingField: lightBlue
        - <Pos>k__BackingField: {x: 7200, y: 11140}
          <RawContent>k__BackingField: <p>Notice the images in the element below.</p>
          <ColorTheme>k__BackingField: lightBlue
        - <Pos>k__BackingField: {x: 6280, y: 10980}
          <RawContent>k__BackingField: <p>This is your story's starting <a target="_blank"
            rel="noopener noreferrer nofollow" href="https://docs.arcweave.com/project-items/elements"><strong>element</strong></a>.
            Double click it to edit its title or content. (In <em>rich text,</em>
            too!)</p>
          <ColorTheme>k__BackingField: lightBlue
        - <Pos>k__BackingField: {x: 8980, y: 10800}
          <RawContent>k__BackingField: <p>This is a <a target="_blank" rel="noopener
            noreferrer nofollow" href="https://docs.arcweave.com/project-items/labels"><strong>label</strong></a>.
            In <strong>Play Mode</strong>, it appears as a player option.</p><p>Labels
            can do more than this; they can also contain <a target="_blank" rel="noopener
            noreferrer nofollow" href="https://docs.arcweave.com/project-items/labels#arcscript-in-labels">code</a>.
            But let's keep it simple for now.</p>
          <ColorTheme>k__BackingField: lightBlue
        - <Pos>k__BackingField: {x: 6740, y: 11300}
          <RawContent>k__BackingField: <p>This is a <a target="_blank" rel="noopener
            noreferrer nofollow" href="https://docs.arcweave.com/project-items/connections"><strong>connetion</strong></a>.
            Connect elements to create the flow of your story.</p>
          <ColorTheme>k__BackingField: lightBlue
        - <Pos>k__BackingField: {x: 6740, y: 11500}
          <RawContent>k__BackingField: '<p>Creating a connection is intuitive: drag
            from any edge of the source element and drop into the target.</p>'
          <ColorTheme>k__BackingField: lightBlue
        - <Pos>k__BackingField: {x: 9180, y: 11300}
          <RawContent>k__BackingField: <p>This is a <a target="_blank" rel="noopener
            noreferrer nofollow" href="https://docs.arcweave.com/project-items/labels"><strong>label</strong></a>.
            In <strong>Play Mode</strong>, it appears as a player option.</p><p>Labels
            can do more than this; they can also contain <a target="_blank" rel="noopener
            noreferrer nofollow" href="https://docs.arcweave.com/project-items/labels#arcscript-in-labels">code</a>.
            But let's keep it simple for now.</p>
          <ColorTheme>k__BackingField: lightBlue
        - <Pos>k__BackingField: {x: 9040, y: 11940}
          <RawContent>k__BackingField: <p>This is a <a target="_blank" rel="noopener
            noreferrer nofollow" href="https://docs.arcweave.com/project-items/labels"><strong>label</strong></a>.
            In <strong>Play Mode</strong>, it appears as a player option.</p><p>Labels
            can do more than this; they can also contain <a target="_blank" rel="noopener
            noreferrer nofollow" href="https://docs.arcweave.com/project-items/labels#arcscript-in-labels">code</a>.
            But let's keep it simple for now.</p>
          <ColorTheme>k__BackingField: lightBlue
        - <Pos>k__BackingField: {x: 9820, y: 12500}
          <RawContent>k__BackingField: <p>Notice how the audio changes here. The
            <em>school</em> audio stops and the <em>festival</em> one starts.</p><p>Click
            on the attached audio assets, to see their settings.</p>
          <ColorTheme>k__BackingField: lightBlue
        - <Pos>k__BackingField: {x: 9800, y: 11760}
          <RawContent>k__BackingField: <p>Notice how the audio changes here. The
            <em>school</em> audio stops and the <em>home</em> one starts.</p><p>Click
            on the attached audio assets, to see their settings.</p>
          <ColorTheme>k__BackingField: lightBlue
        - <Pos>k__BackingField: {x: 9800, y: 10900}
          <RawContent>k__BackingField: <p>Notice how the audio changes here. The
            <em>school</em> audio stops and the <em>festival</em> one starts.</p><p>Click
            on the attached audio assets, to see their settings.</p>
          <ColorTheme>k__BackingField: lightBlue
        - <Pos>k__BackingField: {x: 9480, y: 10340}
          <RawContent>k__BackingField: <p>To change a character's emotion and facial
            expression, you need to create a new component. </p><p>Set the desired
            image asset as the new component's cover.</p><p>Notice how this project
            uses different components for each characters <em>default</em> and <em>smile</em>
            expression.</p>
          <ColorTheme>k__BackingField: pink
        - <Pos>k__BackingField: {x: 7200, y: 11880}
          <RawContent>k__BackingField: <p>The character images are <a target="_blank"
            rel="noopener noreferrer nofollow" href="https://docs.arcweave.com/project-items/components"><strong>components</strong></a>.
            To attach a component, drag it from the <strong>Components</strong> section
            (also in the left sidebar) into the element.</p><p>To change the attached
            components' order, simply drag and drop them relative to each other.</p>
          <ColorTheme>k__BackingField: pink
        - <Pos>k__BackingField: {x: 7640, y: 11720}
          <RawContent>k__BackingField: <p>Click on the attached component to <a target="_blank"
            rel="noopener noreferrer nofollow" href="https://docs.arcweave.com/project-items/components#editing-components">edit
            it</a>.</p><p>You can change its name and cover (as well as add <a target="_blank"
            rel="noopener noreferrer nofollow" href="https://docs.arcweave.com/project-items/attributes">attributes</a>,
            but let's leave this for another tutorial).</p>
          <ColorTheme>k__BackingField: pink
